    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-08-25T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-08-25T06:00:00-05:00" n="380"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d380">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">751G.00/8–2553: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador at Saigon</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HDR1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Heath</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Saigon</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-08-25T19:00:00+08:00"
                            >August 25, 1953—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>334. No distribution outside Department. Personal for <persName corresp="#p_BPW1"
                        >Philip Bonsal</persName> from <persName corresp="#p_HDR1">Heath</persName>.
                        <persName corresp="#p_TMTJH1">Trapnell</persName> tells me that according
                    available intelligence French command thinks it unlikely that Viet Minh will try
                    another invasion in Laos present time and the fact that all Viet Minh divisions
                    are close around Tonkin Delta leads it to believe that there might be an early
                    offensive against Delta. To meet such an offensive, the French have in addition
                    to their static units, a mobile reserve of 18 battalions plus 10 parachute
                    battalions.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_TMTJH1">Trapnell</persName> does not believe French have
                    any plan to undertake any sizeable offensive operation beyond the five limited
                    operations of which Langson (very successful) and Phan Thiet and North Annam
                    (not very successful) were the first three items.</p>
                <p>This telegram marked “No distribution” since understood <persName
                        corresp="#p_TMTJH1">Trapnell</persName> reporting direct <gloss
                        target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HDR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Heath</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
